<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Lyonothamnus</i> <i>floribundus</i> or <i>Quercus</i> <i>tomentella</i> is dominant in the tree canopy with <i>Quercus</i> <i>agrifolia</i> and <i>Rhamnus</i> <i>pirifolia</i>. Shrubs may include <i>Adenostoma</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>catalinae</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>insularis</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>viridissima</i>, <i>Baccharis</i> <i>pilularis</i>, <i>Comarostaphylis</i> <i>diversifolia</i>, <i>Diplacus</i> <i>parviflorus</i>, <i>Heteromeles</i> <i>arbutifolia</i>, <i>Prunus</i> <i>ilicifolia</i> ssp. <i>lyonii</i> or <i>Quercus</i> <i>pacifica</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text"> Trees < 20 m; canopy is continuous. Shrubs are infrequent to moderately continuous. Herbaceous layer is sparse to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Lyonothamnus floribundus</i> > 50% relative cover in the tree canopy (Rodriguez et al. 2017).</li>
		
		<li><i>Quercus tomentella</i> > 50% relative cover in the tree canopy, or co-dominant with <i>Quercus agrifolia</i> or other trees (Rodriguez et al. 2017).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Moist canyons and slopes, concavities,  rarely exposed slopes. Soils are marine sedimentary (including calcareous), granitic, or volcanic substrates.  </div>
</div>

        
